author: Inside Edition
description: Cardi B is being sued by a security guard who claims the rapper "cut her left cheek with a three-inch fingernail" in 2018.
title: Cardi B Sued by Security Guard #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: When newlyweds Bekka and Jaime Ham went outside to take their wedding photos, they found themselves in the middle of the massive dust storm that struck the Phoenix area. Their photographer, Madisen Ruehle, spoke with Inside Edition. The newlyweds fled down the street with their photographer to try to find shelter. That's when a coffee shop owner, Paul Roupas, saw their plight and came to the rescue.
title: Newlyweds Caught in Dust Storm Rescued by Coffee Shop Owner

author: Inside Edition
description: Travis Kelce got down on bended knee on August 10 in the backyard of his $6 million mansion outside Kansas City. He created an enchanted secret garden with over 2,000 flowers around the gazebo. Kelce's dad, Ed Kelce, spilled the secrets about the fairytale proposal. The couple had just finished taping the Kelce Bothers’ "New Heights" podcast. Travis asked Swift's dad, Scott Swift, for her hand in marriage.
title: More Details Emerge About Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce's Engagement

author: Inside Edition
description: It has been 20 years since the devastation of Hurricane Katrina. Approximately 1,400 people lost their lives and it is estimated over 500 residents of New Orleans and the Gulf Coast went missing and were never found. Good Morning America's Robin Roberts, who is from Mississippi, rushed to the Gulf Coast to cover the storm. She first asked where her mother was. Two decades later, Roberts returned to the region for an ABC special airing Friday. Inside Edition covered Katrina 20 years ago, and its aftermath.
title: Remembering Hurricane Katrina 20 Years Later

author: Inside Edition
description: Cardi B returned to a Los Angeles court to face Emani Ellis, a former security guard who is suing her, claiming the singer "cut her left cheek with a three-inch fingernail" and "violently" struck her. The singer is accused of clawing at Ellis' face outside Cardi B's doctor's office when she was pregnant with her first child in 2018. Cardi testified Wednesday she did not harm the security guard and that it was the security guard who started the trouble.
title: Cardi B Testifies in Assault Trial

author: Inside Edition
description: Two children, 8 and 10, were killed and 17 others were injured after a school shooting at Annunciation Catholic School in South Minneapolis during a school mass. It was the first week of class, and the school has just posted photos of students excited to start the new school year. 30 to 50 shots rang out during the attack. Authorities say the shooter took his own life in the school's parking lot.  He has been identified as 23-year-old Robin Westman and has no known criminal history.
title: 2 Children Killed, 17 Injured After Minneapolis School Shooting

author: Inside Edition
description: Majestic Mount Everest. It's the world's highest mountain, but is sometimes referred to as the world's highest dumpster. While adventure-seekers come and go, many leave behind trash, like plastic food containers, oxygen tanks, or climbing gear. One company wants to tackle the problem by sending in their drones. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Drones Clear 600 Pounds of Trash From Mount Everest

author: Inside Edition
description: Donna Adelson is a 75-year-old grandmother accused of orchestrating the assassination of her former son-in-law, Dan Markel.
title: Accused Assassin 'Mastermind' Grandmother's Trial Begins #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: "Maybe we can do something with that?" Stephanie Choi of Los Angeles lives by a mantra of upcycling that has served her well, as it led to the creation of her business, Rewilder. She and her business partner collect over-produced and unwanted textiles and materials to turn them into useful products. As they say, one person's trash is another's business opportunity. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Upcycling Business Finds New Use for Old Waste
